            <article>
              <h1 class="title is-3"><strong>Healthcare</strong></h1>
              <div class="main-content">
                <figure class="issues-icon issues-icon-left">
                  <i class="fa fa-heartbeat"></i>
                </figure>
                <p>Contrary to what we've been told, people can and do die from a lack of healthcare. And we ALL do have a right to healthcare. Healthcare for all can be a reality! We must fill the coverage gaps ASAP, insuring as many as we can by supporting Medicaid Expansion. We must stop the Congressional sabotage that's causing insurance companies to raise our premium costs. Currently, Congress is intentionally withholding the 're-insurance' subsidy payments that they owe insurance companies, which forces them to adjust, causing them to raise their rates to stay in business -  making us think the Affordable Care Act (ACA) is to blame for the rate hikes.</p>
              <br>
              <p> We can strengthen and expand Medicare in phases, covering everyone and lowering costs. We can stabilize the market by fixing the current laws, having Congress actually pay what they promised, then reducing more costs by repealing the Republican's restriction not allowing Medicare to negotiate down drug prices and other services. There is no immediate solution without Republican's help.</p> 
              <br>
              <p>AND, in the meantime, even though this is a state legislative issue, I will do everything I can to support 'Medicaid Expansion' in Idaho, and across the country. It makes NO sense that Idaho is currently refusing to accept what amounts to a 90% discount for providing healthcare for those 78,000+ Idahoans that remain uninsured. And for what reason - misguided pride? <strong>Refusing to expand Medicaid for the 78,000+ Idahoans making less than $12,100, when that Medicaid is 90% paid for is fiscally irresponsible, callous and heartless.</strong> No one should be without healthcare!</p>
              <br>
              <p>While trying to pay back their major donors and the wealthiest 2%, this Congress ignores the fact that providing basic, necessary healthcare is much cheaper than having the uninsured utilizing the most expensive and least efficient portions of our medical system, like hospital emergency rooms.</p> 
              </div>
              <a class="article-learn-more button is-link" data-id="healthcare">Learn more...</a>
              <div class="extra-content is-hidden" data-id="healthcare">
              <div><p> Think of your family, your home, and everything you've worked so hard for; the medical bills from just one serious accident or illness, could wipe away everything you've worked for!</p></div>
          <div><p>What will I Do?
               <l>
                  <li>Fix the flaws in the existing law to keep all insured and providers solvent</li>
                  <li>Continue 're-insurance' subsidies to keep providers on the state exchanges, and our heath insurance costs down</li>
                  <li>End legislative sabotage of the ACA</li>
                  <li>Support <i><a href="https://medicaidforidaho.org/" target="blank"> 'MedicaidforIdaho.org' </a></i> and their upcoming ballot initiative to expand Medicaid and  <i><a href="http://closethegapidaho.org/wp-content/uploads/Chart-Book.pdf" target="_blank"> 'Close the Gap' </a></i> so that Idahoans making less than $12,100/year can get health care coverage</li>
                  <li>Create a healthcare system that works for us ALL - "Consolidated-Medicare".</li>
                  <li>Repeal the law that requires Medicare to pay full price for pharmaceuticals, and which makes it illegal to negotiate for fair and lower prices</li>
                  <li>Repeal laws that forbid Americans from buying cheaper pharmaceuticals from foreign markets</li>
                </l>
             </p></div>
         <div>
         <p>Healthcare doesn't have to be as complicated and expensive as Congress is making it. Starting with Medicare as a model, create <strong>Consolidated Medicare for ALL</strong>, with an accelerated implementation, 'phasing it in' as soon as able. This approach is far more affordable for all, including the taxpayers, and shows that cost-effective healthcare can be a reality. Don’t be fooled by the lies calling this 'socialized medicine' or making this about 'waiting in long lines'- we already do!  Our 'right to life' in this country is a right to a healthy life.  ‘Consolidated-Medicare’ is uniquely American, and will save lives and tax dollars.</p> 
              <p>And please don't be fooled by the greedy top 1% who want more money at our expense. The Republican Healthcare/Tax plan gives the top 1% a huge tax cut and more wealth, so even more people would lose healthcare. According to the latest CBO score, these tax cuts for the wealthy would would exceed the legal $1.5 trillion deficit limits, so their <i>self-imposed deficit increase</i> and would necessitate cutting billions from Medicare!  
<div> As Americans, we embody compassion and humanity for our fellow man and an urge to help others. Those in power are trying to take that away from us - to make us angry or resentful of others who are in need or less fortunate - and yes, trying to destroy our humanity and compassion for one another. We must fight this with everything we've got! </div></p>
              <div>
              <p>Medicare is functional, affordable and respected. In short, it works! Transforming it into 'Consolidated-Medicare' makes it work for all of us.</p>
              </div>
            </article>
            <hr/>
            <a class="anchor-tag" id="public_lands"></a>
            <article>
              <h1 class="title is-3"><strong>Public Lands</strong></h1>
              <div class="main-content">
                <figure class="issues-pic issues-pic-right">
                  <img src="images/issues_environment.jpg"></img>
                </figure>
                <p>Idaho is NOT for sale! Keep public lands public and protected, accessible for hunting, recreation, and for our enjoyment. The State of Idaho cannot afford to maintain and protect these lands like the Federal government does, and our State Legislature already knows this. If the Federal Government is forced to turn control over to the state, Idaho could not afford to maintain them and would have to sell our lands. Then our public lands would be inaccessible and gone forever - We cannot let this happen!</p>
              </div>
              <a class="article-learn-more button is-link" data-id="public-lands">Learn more...</a>
              <div class="extra-content is-hidden" data-id="public-lands">
                <p>Many republicans try to convince us our federal public lands are a “states rights” issue, and that we need to return them to state control, claiming the state can do a better job. This makes absolutely NO sense, because Idaho just doesn't have the money.  So why take on this additional cost and responsibility when the federal government is paying a bill Idaho can’t afford? Could it be the many rich and special business interests want our lands for the profit they can make?  The answer is YES! </p>
                 <li>The Federal government owns and pays to manage 32,621,631 acres in Idaho, which is 61.6% of the land in our state, caring for and maintaining the land that we enjoy.</li>
                  <li>  A recent study reveals Idaho would experience up to a <i>$250 million deficit</i> if Idaho owned and had to pay to manage this land.  How much do you think our State taxes would have to increase to cover what the Federal Government pays for? They pay the costs of timber management, recreation and visitor services, protection of wild horses and indigenous species, including fish & wildlife, road maintenance, plus public safety & fire protection – which in 2015 alone, firefighting cost over $300 million (70% of which the federal government paid). Imagine Idaho being responsible for that entire $300 million.</li>
                  <li>The Republican political stranglehold on Idaho is also giving away public and private land access to Texas gas companies and giving away mineral rights of private landholders  using ‘forced-pooling’ as a tactic to steal resources and our property rights. How is this happening? Our Idaho legislature is passing laws written for them by gas industry lobbyists. So who do they really represent, us or the gas industry?</li>
                  <li>  Republicans are repealing laws that make our rivers safe for fishing, for drinking water, and are creating laws that put our ground water at risk.</li>
              <br/>
             <p><strong>Private Lands -</strong> We must also protect private ownership rights - Our Idaho legislature is giving Alta-Mesa a free ‘fracking’ license to take our privately held mineral rights to our own land, using 'forced pooling' to force land owners into leases that are yielding only a pittance. And no protections have been put in place for when the land or groundwater for wells are poisoned by the chemicals released.</p>
              <div>
                <p> > <i>Since fracking - Oklahoma has more than 3 times the earthquakes as California.</i></li>
              </div>
            <p>Useful links that help explain:</p>
              <ul>
